#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""ambient — CLI for the Ambient (ambient.xyz) OpenAI-compatible inference API.

Commands:
  setup                First-run: paste + verify your API key, store securely
                       (--force rotates, --remove offboards)
  models               List models — READY first, context/capabilities, defaults marked
  use       [model]    Pick the sticky default model (interactive menu if no arg)
  curate    [verb]     Choose which models the menus surface (hide/show/only/note)
  ask       [prompt]   One-shot completion (prompt arg, stdin, or both via '-':
                       cat doc.txt | ambient-codex ask "summarize" -)
  audit     [paths…]   Second-opinion code audit (files as args, diff via
                       stdin, or --repo [DIR] for a whole repository —
                       git-aware walk, upfront file plan)
  map       "<p>" [f…] Bulk lane: run ONE prompt independently over MANY items
                       (files, or stdin lines / --jsonl objects); one result
                       streamed per item, cache-resumable (re-runs re-bill
                       only missing items)
  chat                 Interactive REPL — streams each reply, per-turn token
                       receipt (opt-in savings); /model /clear /help /exit
  code      [task]     Single-file code generation on the code model
  build     [task]     Plan + generate a SET of files (manifest-first; writes
                       only with --apply, inside --dir; never executes)
  agent     [args…]    Interactive agentic terminal on Ambient (opencode TUI)
  doctor               Diagnose: bad key vs out-of-funds vs model availability
                       vs your network vs Ambient itself — names the culprit
  usage     [--days]   Local token-usage summary and optional relative savings
  control              Codex-native control panel: status, mode, models, key,
                       settings, doctor, usage (also exposed through MCP)
  mode      [on|off]   Delegate mode toggle (no arg = status). When ON, Codex
                       routes code writing through Ambient for the session
  link                 Put a stable `ambient-codex` launcher on your PATH
  cache     [action]   Inspect / clear the local chunk cache
  trust-url [url]      Explicitly trust a non-Ambient endpoint (self-hosted)
  version              Print version
  codex     [args…]    Blocked upstream for now — explains why; use `agent`

Inputs beyond a model's single-shot budget are auto map-reduced (parallel
chunk calls + merge) up to the bounded 20M-character input guard. Repository
audits include source files up to that guard and report any larger source or
aggregate-overflow exclusion as PARTIAL coverage.

Exit codes: 0 ok · 1 diagnosed error · 2 PARTIAL result · 3 no key configured
            64 usage error · 130 interrupted

Credentials: OS keychain `ambient-codex` (preferred) or ~/.config/ambient-codex/env
             (chmod 600). State root override: AMBIENT_CODEX_HOME.
Model resolution: -m flag > AMBIENT_MODEL_MAP phase entry > AMBIENT_MODEL /
                  AMBIENT_CODE_MODEL env var > saved default (ambient use)
                  > built-in default. `-m auto[:cheapest|:largest]` (or
                  `ambient use auto`) delegates the pick to the live catalog
                  — resolved per call, always printed. AMBIENT_MODEL_MAP
                  (like AMBIENT_MAX_PARALLEL, env or
                  config) routes phases: "map=ID,reduce=ID,chat=ID,code=ID";
                  --reduce-model overrides its reduce entry per run.
An explicit concrete -m model is NEVER silently swapped (SACRED) — routing
is advisory, auto is explicit delegation, --fallback stays opt-in.
"""

